552
01:23:00.860 --> 01:23:22.220
Raúl Kripalani: There could be… this could be a spam or amplification vector where malicious actors could potentially bundle any attestations that they see on the wire and form new aggregates and spam the network with those. So the simple solution is, at the network level, we only allow single attestations. Now, the reality of the network is that we have…

553
01:23:23.340 --> 01:23:31.710
Raúl Kripalani: we have aggregates of validators. We have operators in the network of different types, that are together,

