01:31:48.070 --> 01:32:08.000
Raúl Kripalani: authorization. So, if we were to remove the batch seal mechanism, which is something we considered, then you could potentially have a malicious actor that is aggregating… that is taking two aggregates and forming a super aggregate, and at that point, the beacon chain… the beacon client would need to

604
01:32:08.410 --> 01:32:24.580
Raúl Kripalani: would need to identify which is the stronger one, and it becomes more… the validation function becomes more complex. This is actually an open point. I do wanna… I do wanna delve into this a little bit more. I think it merits a little bit more consideration before we completely discard it.

605
01:32:26.310 --> 01:32:36.840
Raúl Kripalani: But yeah, those are… those are the main, validation rules that we need to introduce, in addition to the… the existing ones that are… that are more structural.

